## Scope
main.js only

## Goal
Ensure all emitters always have a valid sound object when samples are assigned

---

## Step 1 — Fix sample assignment path

FIND where samples are dropped / assigned to lines or segments

ENSURE:

    object.sound = buildSoundConfig(file);

This MUST happen at assignment time

---

## Step 2 — Safety fallback at spawn

In BOTH emitter functions:

ADD before using source.sound:

    if (!source.sound) {
        console.warn('Missing sound on emitter source', source);
        return;
    }

---

## Step 3 — Validate sound object structure

Ensure buildSoundConfig returns:

    {
        buffer: AudioBuffer,
        midi: { note: number },
        rootNote: number
    }

---

## Step 4 — Do NOT allow partial sound objects

Add guard:

    if (!sound.buffer) return;

---

## Step 5 — Debug log (temporary)

Inside playback trigger:

    console.log('PLAY', {
        note: sound.midi?.note,
        root: sound.rootNote,
        hasBuffer: !!sound.buffer
    });

---

## Expected Result

- Lines with samples ALWAYS produce sound
- Silent lines = truly empty (not broken)
- No invisible failures

---

## Implementation Guide

- Where: sample assignment + emitter spawn
- Run: reload app
- Expect: immediate sound when emitter active